\binom{5}{3} = 10
(\dfrac{1}{2})^6 = \dfrac{1}{64}
10(\dfrac{1}{64}) = \dfrac{5}{32}
P(A\mbox{ wins at 6th g. | series ends at 6th g.})=\frac{P(A\mbox{ wins at 6th g. and series ends at 6th g.})}{P(\mbox{series ends at 6th g.})}
=\frac{P(A\mbox{ wins at 6th g.})}{P(\mbox{series ends at 6th g.})}
=\frac{P(A\mbox{ wins at 6th g.})}{P(A\mbox{ wins at 6th})+P(B\mbox{ wins at 6th)}}
=\frac{5/32}{5/32+5/32}=1/2
